If any of you are having a hard time with heartbreak and/or narcissistic abuse, remember the significance that comes with your presence. Thieves do not rob empty homes. Just don’t let them extinguish the light in you that attracted them in the first place. Here are some of my breakup affirmations that have really helped me get through this rough transition:

1. I am not perfect but I didn’t deserve the treatment I received
2. I stayed true to myself and to my values and as a result the relationship ended. I will not feel shame about speaking on the things I care about and I will not let it prevent me from speaking my truth in the future
3. The things I did and said to set boundaries and express my needs would not have pushed away the right person; what I lost was not meant for me
4. I am a woman of virtue, substance, character and integrity, and I am a woman of my word. It’s ok to expect the same out of my partner
5. I am a valuable person, I just wasn’t valued by one specific person
6. I have no shame about staying true to my authentic self. Narcissistic abusers have to live in the shame of leading disingenuous lives. It’s not my responsibility to change them or “love” them through it
7. I am an asset to any relationship; the relationship lost its value now that I am no longer in it and my absence is surely felt. I will become stronger from this experience and will bring even more value to the next relationship I’m in
8. I pull my weight and did my part as a dedicated partner; I have what it takes to succeed in a healthy lifelong relationship with the right person. It’s ok that my ex partner did not and it’s not a reflection of my value or who I am. What I can do better is recognize the signs of harmful behavior sooner than I did
9. He is not who I thought he was in the end, but the loss I experienced was real. It’s ok to feel heartbreak as long as I acknowledge that the relationship wasn’t meant for me. Committing to my healing process doesn’t give him any more power. It’s important for me to talk about it and embrace recovery
10. Now is the time to breathe, grow and continue creating; my energy is healthy and flowing and I will continue to thrive
What goes unexplored will remain a mystery ✨unavailable, untouchable, unbothered ✌🏽
It’s not an easy life… but it’s a beautiful one ✨🌦️
